                    </tr>
                </table>
            </div>

            <div class="section">
                <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
                <p>Burger Stacking Game collects and processes the following categories of information to provide and improve our gaming services:</p>
                
                <div class="data-types">
                    <div class="data-type-item">
                        <div class="data-type-title">Game Progress Data</div>
                        <div class="data-type-desc">We collect information about your gameplay including scores, levels completed, achievements unlocked, and game preferences to save your progress and provide a personalized gaming experience.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="data-type-item">
                        <div class="data-type-title">Device Information</div>
                        <div class="data-type-desc">We collect basic device information including device model, operating system version, unique device identifiers, and mobile network information to ensure the game functions properly on your device.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="data-type-item">
                        <div class="data-type-title">Usage Data</div>
                        <div class="data-type-desc">We collect information about how you interact with the game, including features used, session duration, in-game actions, and technical error logs to improve user experience and game performance.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="data-type-item">
                        <div class="data-type-title">Advertising Data</div>
                        <div class="data-type-desc">Information collected by our advertising partners to display relevant advertisements, including device identifiers and interaction with ads.</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="section">
                <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
                <p>The information collected is used for the following purposes:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Game Functionality:</strong> To provide core gameplay features, save your progress, and ensure the game operates as intended</li>
                    <li><strong>Personalization:</strong> To customize your gaming experience based on your preferences and gameplay history</li>
                    <li><strong>Game Improvement:</strong> To analyze gameplay patterns, identify bugs, balance game difficulty, and improve game performance and features</li>
                    <li><strong>Technical Support:</strong> To diagnose technical issues and provide customer support when needed</li>
                    <li><strong>Advertising:</strong> To display relevant advertisements and measure ad performance</li>
                    <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> To understand how players engage with the game and optimize the user experience</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="section">
                <h2>3. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
                <p>We respect your privacy and do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information to third parties for their marketing purposes. We may share information only in the following circumstances:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> With third-party service providers who assist us in operating the game (such as advertising networks and analytics providers), subject to confidentiality agreements</li>
                    <li><strong>Legal Requirements:</strong> When required by law, legal process, or government request</li>
                    <li><strong>Protection of Rights:</strong> To protect our rights, property, or safety, or that of our users or others</li>
                    <li><strong>Business Transfers:</strong> In connection with a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, where user information may be transferred</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="section">
                <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
                <p>Burger Stacking Game integrates the following third-party services that may collect and process data:</p>
                
                <h3>Google AdMob</h3>
                <p>The game uses Google AdMob to display advertisements. AdMob may collect and use data including device identifiers, IP address, and usage information in accordance with Google's Privacy Policy. This data is used to provide personalized advertising experiences.</p>
                
                <div class="important-notice">
                    <p><strong>Important:</strong> For detailed information about how Google collects and processes data, please review the <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">Google Privacy Policy</a> and <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites" target="_blank">How Google uses information from sites or apps that use our services</a>.</p>
                </div>

                <p>You can control personalized advertising through your device settings or by visiting Google's <a href="https://adssettings.google.com/" target="_blank">Ads Settings</a>.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="section">
                <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
                <p>We implement appropriate technical and organizational security measures to protect your information against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. These measures include:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Encryption of data in transit and at rest where applicable</li>
                    <li>Regular security assessments and updates</li>
                    <li>Access controls and authentication mechanisms</li>
                    <li>Secure data storage practices</li>
                </ul>
                <p>However, please note that no method of electronic transmission or storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="section">
                <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
                <p>We retain your information only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy, unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law. Game progress data is retained while you continue to use the game. When data is no longer needed, we will securely delete or anonymize it.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="section">
                <h2>7. Your Rights and Choices</h2>
                <p>Depending on your location, you may have the following rights regarding your personal information:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Access:</strong> Request access to the personal information we hold about you</li>
                    <li><strong>Correction:</strong> Request correction of inaccurate or incomplete information</li>
                    <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> Request deletion of your personal information and game data</li>
                    <li><strong>Data Portability:</strong> Request a copy of your data in a structured, machine-readable format</li>
                    <li><strong>Opt-Out:</strong> Opt-out of personalized advertising through device settings</li>
                    <li><strong>Withdrawal of Consent:</strong> Withdraw consent where processing is based on consent</li>
                </ul>
                <p>To exercise these rights, please contact us using the information provided in the Contact Us section below.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="section">
                <h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
                <p>Burger Stacking Game is designed to be family-friendly and may be played by children. We are committed to complying with the Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA) and similar regulations worldwide.</p>
                <p>We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13 without verifiable parental consent. The game does not require account creation or collection of personal information to play. If we become aware that we have collected information from a child under 13 without proper consent, we will take steps to delete such information promptly.</p>
                <p>Parents or guardians who believe their child has provided personal information can contact us to request deletion.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="section">
                <h2>9. International Data Transfers</h2>
                <p>Your information may be transferred to and processed in countries other than your country of residence. These countries may have data protection laws that differ from those in your country. We ensure appropriate safeguards are in place to protect your information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="section">
                <h2>10. In-App Purchases</h2>
                <p>The game may offer in-app purchases for additional content or features. All payment processing is handled by the Google Play Store or Apple App Store, and we do not collect or store payment information. Please refer to Google's or Apple's privacy policies for information about how payment data is handled.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="section">
                <h2>11. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
                <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices, technology, legal requirements, or other factors. When we make changes, we will:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Update the "Effective Date" at the top of this policy</li>
                    <li>Notify you through the game or by other means if required by law</li>
                    <li>Obtain your consent if required for material changes</li>
                </ul>
                <p>We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically to stay informed about how we protect your information.</p>
            </div>

